d was a great climber and co-founder of the Alpine Club of Canada. Mapper of Mountains also tells the story of the Rocky Mountain Repeat Photography Project, which studies the changes sustained in the Rockies, repeating the field work accomplished by Bridgland almost a century ago.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCartographerszCanadavBiography. 0aMountain mappingzAlbertazJasper National ParkxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhotographic surveyingxHistoryy20th century. 0aSurveyorszCanadavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aBiography.1 aHiggs, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZezulka-Mailloux, Gabrielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088864764140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780888647641423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780888647641/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles